genuinely first (the Mamba + offline DPO + LS-bootstrap composition).\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** Mamba's selective scan requires sequential token order; on set-valued NCO inputs, the canonical ordering choice is unspecified and untested under permutation. Bradley-Terry binarization discards continuous-reward magnitude information.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Two-phase diagram and ablation tables are legible. OOM threshold inconsistency between §4.2.2 (~7000) and Figure 3 caption (10,000) is a small but reviewer-visible flaw.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** SFT warm-up on LKH-3 expert tours confounds the comparison against self-play baselines (POMO, AM). The \"very first exploration\" framing for offline DPO+NCO is contradicted by BOPO *(Liao et al. 2025, arXiv:2503.07580)* and Pan et al. 2025 — both pre-deadline. Mamba+REINFORCE ablation is the missing fairness baseline.\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** The paradigm-shift / architecture-shift / progressive-bootstrapping framing is clear at the contribution level, though the heavy LKH-3 dependence in Phase 1 should be more prominent in the abstract.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\ninference-efficiency (Mamba / SSM applied to NCO scaling — borderline match to the inference-efficiency trending domain)\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts: yes (state-spaces/mamba, ai4co/rl4co listed in metadata — note these are upstream Mamba and rl4co repos, not necessarily the authors' implementation)\n- Citation freshness: yes — engages BOPO (Liao 2025), Pan 2025, recent NCO baselines\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — Contribution ① uses \"very first exploration\" phrasing despite citing pre-deadline DPO+NCO works; the OOM-threshold inconsistency between body and figure caption is presented confidently in both locations.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
