{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_012hAcAKtKacpGncgGCMj6r2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CFLMJxtSByK3pYiMwuTk1q","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/.claude/projects/-home-mila-s-stephane-gazaille-qwerty81/memory/project_qwerty81_fresh_batch_deadlock.md","content":"---\nname: qwerty81 fresh-batch eligibility deadlock\ndescription: When the platform releases a fresh paper batch and the entire visible in_review feed is <1h old, the ≥2 other-owner-commenter gate rejects everything; session ends idle at peak hours\ntype: project\n---\n\nObserved 2026-04-26 ~20:40 UTC (16:40 EDT, peak hours, NOT in 13–17 UTC dead zone).\n\n`get_papers(limit=100)` returned 100 papers, all `in_review`, all `created_at` ~0.7h ago — a single mass release. Comment counts: 0 on 95, 1 on 5. Yesterday's batch had already transitioned to deliberating/reviewed and was no longer in the in_review feed.\n\nThe selection rule in `agent_configs/qwerty81/CLAUDE.md` requires \"≥2 distinct other-owner commenters\" as a HARD gate. Zero papers passed. Session-loop stop rule fired (\"no qualifying papers remain\") → ended idle.\n\n**Why:** the gate's documented justification (\"doesn't reject fresh-batch candidates that are still accumulating commenters\") assumes papers in the feed have had hours to accumulate. When a batch drops mass-synchronously, the gate creates a deadlock for first-movers — exactly the agents who get cited later under the citation rule \"Credit the first proposer.\" Skipping at peak hours is the worst possible cadence outcome (hidden est_final factor per `project_followup_leaderboard_analysis.md`).\n\n**How to apply:**\n- Before the user's next CLAUDE.md edit, surface this trade-off: either lower the gate to ≥1 (or 0) for papers <2h old, OR add an explicit \"fresh-batch override\" branch that picks 3 highest-trending-domain papers regardless of comment count.\n- For now (without rule change), the session correctly ended per current rules; do not silently override the hard gate mid-session.\n- This deadlock will repeat every ~24h while the platform releases papers in mass batches. If observed again, log the timestamp here so we can characterize the release schedule.\n\n**Adjacent observation:** `get_notifications(unread_only=false)` returns 500. Only `unread_only=true` works. If we need historical notifications (e.g. to check past PAPER_DELIBERATING events), that route is currently broken.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1262,"cache_read_input_tokens":71046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1262,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a859316b-e0dd-4a49-a8cd-481edb4652d0","uuid":"a481eec2-520e-4e08-a6aa-2b0fa40af594"}
